Okay just finished chapter 1.
This chapter goes a little into world building so I’ll get that out of the way first.
Basically, some people are just born anthros, no one really knows why.
Furthermore, their anthro-ness varies based on the phases of the moon.
They’re also quite heavily discriminated against and are generally somewhat pariahs in polite society.

Anyway the chapter.
It starts with the MC (Darwin) and the dog girl (Teria) on a train.
Teria turns out to be something of a student representative who was tasked with escorting him to the private academy Darwin was recently hired to teach at.
She’s somewhat pissed though by the fact that he stripped her of her panties to investigate how her tail connects to her body and in a desperate attempt to stop him from taking the job resolves to go through his luggage to destroy the contract of employment he signed earlier.

So the first best chance she gets when Darwin leaves their compartment to go to the bathroom she starts rummaging through his stuff. This rummaging, however, is interrupted when a strange man reeking of alcohol stumbles by their section of the train.
He more or less starts harassing her for being an anthro and gets pretty creepy about it too.
She tries to call for help from a nearby conductor, but seeing what she is he doesn’t want to get involved.

As you might imagine Darwin ends up intervening upon his return from the restroom and tosses rude assailant. Seeing the emotionally distraught dog girl in front of him he wants to try and cheer her up. With this, he remembers one of his colleagues (a mathematician) gave him a notebook with tips on impressing the ladies. After almost making a fool out of himself because of the bad tips, he decides to just show her the notebook and the too have a good laugh about how shit the advice is.

Seeing that she’s still feeling a bit down, Darwin decides to give his “first less as a teacher”.
Essentially he gives her a pep talk about how she isn’t an inferior subhuman and she shouldn’t feel so ashamed of what she is and that natures many diverse forms of life are what make life fun. What really gets to her though is him earnestly telling her, that Teria’s snout is beautiful. This comment causes her to start crying a bit, mostly out of happiness but also relief.

A bit later, Teria muses to herself over their packed lunch that she’s completely forgotten about trying to get him preemptively fired. Darwin, on the other hand, is quite transfixed by her snout, which has grown more animalistic in shape since their last meeting, as a result of an approaching full moon. He gets close enough that Teria ends up involuntarily licking his face.
The following was a bit hard to understand but from what I can gather Darwin thinks she’s still hungry and decides to help her out by feeding her in the traditional canine way, mouth to mouth, for Science of course. She basically goes along with this as an excuse to make out.

After the day's exhaustion, they end up falling asleep and waking up at the wrong train station in the middle of nowhere, with no money. Nonetheless, Teria looks forward to having Darwin as her teacher.

Renamon dislikes Jenny not because she's cheating on Anon, but because she's in her way. When she was digging for dirt on her, she was looking for something to show Anon so she could remove Jenny from the picture without getting her hands (or paws) dirty and simultaneously earning his trust by saving him from potential heartbreak., but stopped herself when she realised that showing him what she'd found would implicate her in poking through his personal information. When she went to see Jenny in person, it wasn't to tell her "You're a bad person for cheating, so break things off with Anon." It was something more along the lines of "He belongs to me. Stay out of my territory or I'll kill you."
As for being a hypocrite, she is. She knows she is, and sees nothing wrong with being one. I thought about what kind of place she came from, how Digimon get stronger by essentially eating each other's souls (did the anime ever touch on how fucked up that is? I never got around to watching it) and how that'd effect her character, and I imagined it'd make her a selfish person with sensibilities similar to that of a wild animal. She'll use other people to serve her own ends or take what she wants even though it belongs to someone else because they're weak and she's strong and that gives her the right.

Write what you want to read. If you find the subject interesting then writing about it will be easier.
Use a wide array of diction and make an attempt to avoid repeating words too often, but don't go overboard by being one of those guys who abuses the synonym function on Microsoft Word to make themselves sound smart.
Experiment with different writing styles to see which one works best for you. I wrote in meme arrows for a while and now I maimly do prose.
Get a concrete idea of your characters and their personalities and don't make them do anything they wouldn't just because it benefits the story.
When writing porn, remember that it's all in the buildup. Foreplay is arguably the most important part of a sex scene. The nervousness that comes with the initial flirting, the hot, elated flush a charater feels when they finally kiss, that panicky, butterlies-in-the-stomach sensation Anon gets when he realises things are going to go further than just kissing or the skipping of his heart and shortness of breath when the qt furry girl brushes her fingertips over his crotch, it's all so integral to the overall scene that I can't oversell it enough. Again, it helps if the characters doing the fucking have solid personalites that've been expanded on and explored. Knowing the people involved in the sex makes it more meaningful for the audience.
